{"cells":[{"metadata":{"_uuid":"c35dfbaf5fe29558a36acbf0fc1e435b98184d95","_cell_guid":"9bf3b4fe-f5b7-88cc-6d6b-2662dfa29fd3"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Happiness Index vs Terrorism!\n-----------------------------\nVamsi Krishna | "},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"2fce091baaa5a24aa31e654cc119264bc1e8cc5a","_cell_guid":"975e862a-d96e-4851-88fb-fad8441fd78b"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":""},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"68a1bbe7ccab7f3ae9c09c1104f5ebfaf6a8a659","_cell_guid":"0bc8b9b2-fe6b-ff09-f52a-728173e9c762","_execution_state":"idle","trusted":true},"cell_type":"code","source":"# This R environment comes with all of CRAN preinstalled, as well as many other helpful packages\n# The environment is defined by the kaggle/rstats docker image: https://github.com/kaggle/docker-rstats\n# For example, here's several helpful packages to load in \n\nlibrary(ggplot2) # Data visualization\nlibrary(readr) # CSV file I/O, e.g. the read_csv function\n\n# Input data files are available in the \"../input/\" directory.\n# For example, running this (by clicking run or pressing Shift+Enter) will list the files in the input directory\n\nlist.files(\"../input\")\nlist.files(\"../input/gtd\")\nHappiness<- read.csv(\"../input/world-happiness/2015.csv\")\nterrorism <- read.csv(\"../input/gtd/globalterrorismdb_0617dist.csv\")\n\n# Any results you write to the current directory are saved as output.\nlibrary(ggplot2)\nlibrary(rworldmap)\nlibrary(dplyr)\nlibrary(corrplot)\n\n# Any results you write to the current directory are saved as output.","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"181b54cc95faac21f415eac27885f2e900da4b2b","_cell_guid":"5b1338ba-3710-4b1c-a899-7076600ad6b9","_execution_state":"idle","collapsed":true,"trusted":false},"cell_type":"code","source":"terrorism<-terrorism[terrorism$iyear==\"2015\",]\ncolnames(terrorism)[9] <- \"Country\"\nHappiness$Country <- as.character(Happiness$Country)\nterrorism$Country<- as.character(terrorism$Country)\nHappiness <-Happiness[which(!is.na(Happiness$Country)),]\ncorrection<-c(\"Congo (Brazzaville)\"=\"Democratic Republic of the Congo\",\"Congo (Kinshasa)\"=\"Republic of Congo\",\"United States\"=\"USA\",\"United Kingdom\"= \"UK\")\nfor(i in names(correction)){\n      Happiness[Happiness$Country==i,\"Country\"]<-correction[i]\n}\n\n\nq<-map_data(\"world\")\ncolnames(q)[5] <- \"Country\"\ndf<- left_join(q,Happiness)\n","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"51361a35acaea78d07185b446d3168087748b55a","_cell_guid":"93a51cf2-06f3-4b56-a162-23f1ee5a3480","_execution_state":"idle"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Happiness score vs Number of terror attacks on civilians (2015)\n---------------------------------------------------------------"},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"9ceac5b8502fab84e00013c035317bd7d41cd986","_cell_guid":"aa5d59d2-0b79-4bad-850b-bad46c781718","_execution_state":"idle","collapsed":true,"trusted":false},"cell_type":"code","source":"\n\nBombing<- terrorism[terrorism$attacktype1==3,]\ntarget_citizen<- terrorism[terrorism$targsubtype1==75|terrorism$targsubtype1==67,] ##  Unnamed Civilian/Unspecified  or Village/City/Town/Suburb \n\nggplot()  +\n  geom_polygon( aes(x = df$long, y = df$lat, group = df$group,fill= df$Happiness.Score)) + \n  coord_equal() +scale_fill_gradient(breaks=c(3,5,7,9)) +\n  geom_point(aes(target_citizen$longitude,target_citizen$latitude,shape=\".\"))+\n  ggtitle(\"Happiness score vs Number of terror attacks on civilians (2015)\")+\n    xlab(\"\") + ylab(\"\") + guides(shape=FALSE) + labs(fill=\"Happiness Score\")\n\n\n","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"8e07182d18f2d7ed3736280a9bcf850c5d0f9f30","_cell_guid":"632ca85d-20b1-4827-84c6-e7d16c8318a9","_execution_state":"idle"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Correlating all the variables contributing to Happiness and Terror attacks!\n------------------------------------------------------------------------"},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"3a88adf0042b1cf3647765c3a2cc1a6ab129f4ea","_cell_guid":"da97a37e-80e1-4c94-ae2b-dd5c897049df","_execution_state":"idle"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"In the graph below we can clearly see the strong negative correlation between happiness score, Family and freedom with terror attacks.\n"},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"a50aa0cd9d905c996b7d4752de6a15e40861354e","_cell_guid":"1b99532b-fcbf-4323-b563-ff9459a55ff7","_execution_state":"idle","collapsed":true,"trusted":false},"cell_type":"code","source":"corr_data<-Happiness %>% left_join(terrorism) %>% \ngroup_by(Country,Happiness.Score,Economy..GDP.per.Capita.,Family,Health..Life.Expectancy.,Freedom,Trust..Government.Corruption.,Generosity,Dystopia.Residual) %>% \nsummarise(Terror_attack = length(eventid))\n\ncorrplot(cor(corr_data[,3:10]))","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"e636b99845a4ba57337ab90d5f5739b2244f455c","_cell_guid":"158afdd8-c6a2-4c0a-8093-6d329333277c","_execution_state":"idle","collapsed":true,"trusted":false},"cell_type":"code","source":"Happiness %>% left_join(terrorism) %>% group_by(Country,Happiness.Rank) %>%\n  summarise(Terror_attack = length(eventid)) %>% ggplot()+ aes(Happiness.Rank,Terror_attack) + \n  geom_smooth(method = \"loess\") +\n  ggtitle(\"Happiness Rank vs Terror attacks\") + ylab(\"No. of Terror Attacks\")","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"b63bb8ae8a6ae77c1b59132d69f906c555f1b867","_cell_guid":"54893f02-3269-465a-a5dd-6c9e40b875a5","_execution_state":"idle"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Sense of Freedom and Terror attacks\n-----------------------------------\n**Here Freedom is on the scale of 0 to 1, where 1 means a state of complete, unwavering freedom!**\n"},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"3435fb0a2660e4967b3783d4cbd494a527bd0001","_cell_guid":"fa196c75-3555-4294-b5b2-4764e09fb188","_execution_state":"idle","collapsed":true,"trusted":false},"cell_type":"code","source":"Happiness %>% left_join(terrorism) %>% group_by(Country,Freedom) %>%\n  summarise(Terror_attack = length(eventid)) %>% ggplot()+ aes(Freedom,Terror_attack) + \n  geom_smooth(method = \"loess\") +\n  ggtitle(\" Sense of Freedom vs Terror attacks\") + ylab(\"No. of Terror Attacks\")","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"0f5c74fe22df89ed3641d2bf1b0412250104218d","_cell_guid":"d6321288-9175-4bd2-bd24-5d3befc2c974","_execution_state":"idle"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Dystopia and Terrorism!\n-----------------------"},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"187844bf5ad41ca225f705fa9fd8784063a3e6d5","_cell_guid":"03808829-7b4e-466e-8ab4-af78aa588fe5","_execution_state":"idle"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**What is Dystopia?**\n\nDystopia is an imaginary country that has the world’s least-happy people. The purpose in establishing Dystopia is to have a benchmark against which all countries can be favorably compared (no country performs more poorly than Dystopia) in terms of each of the six key variables, thus allowing each sub-bar to be of positive width. The lowest scores observed for the six key variables, therefore, characterize Dystopia. Since life would be very unpleasant in a country with the world’s lowest incomes, lowest life expectancy, lowest generosity, most corruption, least freedom and least social support, it is referred to as “Dystopia,” in contrast to Utopia."},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"4d6d39fb7e3a2a44ac521512e891540f19564e1d","_cell_guid":"9bd13e84-6d8b-4303-b3c7-1e05db70f0f2","_execution_state":"idle","trusted":true},"cell_type":"code","source":"Happiness %>% left_join(terrorism) %>% group_by(Country,Dystopia.Residual) %>% \n  summarise(Terror_attack = length(eventid)) %>% ggplot() +aes(Dystopia.Residual,Terror_attack) +geom_smooth(size=1.5,color=\"red\")+\n  xlab(\"Dystopia and Residual\") + ylab(\" No. of Terror Attacks\")+ ggtitle(\"Dystopia and Terrorism!\")","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"02d0025fb76330c823b839ac339c1f6d1a6d64ee","_cell_guid":"33b0d0e5-98e2-4570-9b83-549020573ff2","_execution_state":"idle","collapsed":true,"trusted":false},"cell_type":"code","source":"Happiness %>% left_join(terrorism) %>% group_by(Happiness.Rank) %>% \n    summarise(Terror_attack = length(eventid)) %>% ggplot(aes(Happiness.Rank,Terror_attack)) +\ngeom_bar(stat=\"identity\") ","execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"metadata":{"_uuid":"a9e41e49f06e4c5d7d69e2618cc618dc61a2686a","_cell_guid":"cee2f7e2-0097-492e-bb2c-49ec02673691","_execution_state":"idle"},"cell_type":"markdown","source":"More to Come! Upvote if you like these visualizations\n-----------------------------------------------------"}],"metadata":{"_change_revision":0,"_is_fork":false,"kernelspec":{"display_name":"R","language":"R","name":"ir"},"language_info":{"mimetype":"text/x-r-source","name":"R","pygments_lexer":"r","version":"3.4.2","file_extension":".r","codemirror_mode":"r"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":1}